parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tread separation and tire failure can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Continuous tire thumping or loud thumping noise
vibration while driving
tire tread peeling off
tire blowout
tire shredding
and loss of tire air pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature wear of the inner brake pads can lead to extended stopping distances, reduced braking performance, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake pedal goes to the floor
excessive wear on the inside of brake pads without warning
inner brake pads wear out before outer brake pads
rotors grind before squealing for warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door hinge can cause the door to become misaligned, making it difficult to open or close, and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The door hinge breaks or seizes
the door is difficult to open or close
excessive force is required to close the door
the door becomes misaligned.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can lead to a loss of restraint, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle fails to latch or unlatch
the buckle breaks or cracks
the buckle is difficult to operate
the seat belt is not securely fastened.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to malfunction, leading to a loss of restraint and increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt does not retract properly
the seat belt is stuck in the retracted position
the seat belt does not lock in place
the seat belt is loose or does not provide adequate tension.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Improper installation of the seat belt can lead to a loss of restraint, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt is not securely attached to the vehicle
the seat belt is missing bolts or washers
the seat belt is not properly anchored to the vehicle floor.
